{
  "name": "MC3 Zip Blinds – Admin Document Ingestion → Supabase RAG",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 📚 MC3 Admin Document Ingestion Flow\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Admin uploads a document (PDF/DOCX/TXT/CSV) via the Customer Admin Website\n2. The Admin Website calls POST `/webhook/mc3-admin-ingest` with the file + metadata\n3. n8n receives the file, extracts text via Default Data Loader\n4. OpenAI Embeddings converts text chunks into vectors\n5. Supabase Vector Store inserts the vectors into the `mc3_documents` table\n\n**Webhook URL (Production):**\n`POST /webhook/mc3-admin-ingest`\n\n**Required Supabase Setup:**\nRun the SQL in the sticky note below to create the `mc3_documents` table with `pgvector` extension.",
        "height": 380,
        "width": 580,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "493fca69-581e-47ff-96fa-6d0aec264b6d",
      "name": "📋 README",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        0,
        0
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### 📦 Supabase Table Setup (run once in Supabase SQL Editor)\n\nCREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;\n\nCREATE TABLE mc3_documents (\n  id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  content TEXT,\n  metadata JSONB,\n  embedding VECTOR(1536)\n);\n\nCREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION match_mc3_documents(\n  query_embedding VECTOR(1536),\n  match_count INT DEFAULT 5,\n  filter JSONB DEFAULT '{}'\n) RETURNS TABLE (\n  id BIGINT, content TEXT, metadata JSONB, similarity FLOAT\n) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$\nBEGIN\n  RETURN QUERY\n  SELECT id, content, metadata,\n    1 - (embedding <=> query_embedding) AS similarity\n  FROM mc3_documents\n  WHERE metadata @> filter\n  ORDER BY embedding <=> query_embedding\n  LIMIT match_count;\nEND;\n$$;",
        "height": 420,
        "width": 520,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "5dae1eb9-bdf8-4600-aae4-b105f5bdf21d",
      "name": "🛢️ Supabase SQL Setup",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
